  "texts": [
    "Although CB and CF approaches are more popular in practical applications, both suffer from some limitations.",
    "For instance, the CB filtering approach tends to result in overspecialization with which the diversity in the recommendation results eventually vanishes, while the CF approach suffers from data sparsity and scalability problems.",
    "Moreover, both approaches encounter a significant challenge known as the 'cold-start problem'.",
    "This problem arises when making recommendations to new users and/or items for which the available information is limited.",
    "As a result, the recommendations offered in such cases tend to be of poor quality and lack usefulness."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}